  <!-- Applications -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="apps-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Applications</div>
      <h2 id="apps-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        Drag Chain Conveyor <span class="text-accent">Applications</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p><strong class="text-ink">Grain and feed handling:</strong> En-masse drag conveyors transfer grain between storage bins, dryers, cleaners, and <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">packaging equipment</a>. The enclosed trough prevents grain contamination and dust emission. Multiple inlet and discharge gates along the trough serve multiple bins from a single conveyor run. Feed mills use drag chain conveyors to move ingredients between mixers, pelletizers, and bagging stations.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Snack food and cereal:</strong> Tubular drag conveyors move fragile finished products , chips, crackers, cereals, nuts , from processing to packaging with minimal breakage. The gentle plug-flow movement preserves product integrity. A single tubular drag system replaces multiple belt conveyors and bucket elevators that would break fragile products at each transfer point.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Chemical powder transfer:</strong> En-masse and tubular drag conveyors move chemical powders, catalysts, and additives between reactors, dryers, classifiers, and packaging. The enclosed design prevents operator exposure to hazardous dusts and prevents product contamination. Stainless steel construction handles corrosive chemicals. Explosion-proof drives and inerting systems address combustible dust hazards.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Cement and mineral processing:</strong> Heavy-duty en-masse drag conveyors move cement, fly ash, calcium carbonate, and mineral powders at high capacity. The <a href="/conveyor-types/chain-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">chain conveyor</a> construction handles abrasive materials better than belt conveyors in enclosed applications. Drag chain conveyors feed <a href="/conveyor-types/bucket-elevators/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">bucket elevators</a>, silos, and packaging lines.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Pet food manufacturing:</strong> Tubular drag conveyors handle finished pet food kibble from extruders and coaters to packaging. The gentle handling preserves kibble shape and coating integrity. The sealed tube prevents cross-contamination between flavors and recipes. Quick-clean features (split tube sections, removable discs) facilitate sanitation between product changeovers.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Pharmaceutical ingredients:</strong> Tubular drag conveyors in stainless steel construction move pharmaceutical powders, granules, and tablets in contained environments. The sealed tube meets containment requirements for active pharmaceutical ingredients (APIs). Clean-in-place (CIP) capability allows thorough cleaning between batches. The gentle handling preserves tablet coatings and reduces fines generation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Selection and Maintenance -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim bg-dots" aria-labelledby="selection-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
